The evidence with the title 'Why tax cuts won't generate as much economic growth as Trump ... ' says Oct 18, 2017  ... Despite high hopes , tax reform isn't likely to push up economic growth very much.  ... Already the U.S. gross national debt has more than doubled since the mid- 1980s , to more than 100% of the nation's gross domestic product. In the past, most tax cuts in America have come when the economy was slumping  ... 
